{"blocks":[{"key":"arv6g","text":"Optional: proceed with culture confirmation for samples with a Salmonella (FAM) Ct detected","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":63,"length":10}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"e0ort","text":"Move the rack(s) to a 40-44oC incubator, with shaking preferred. Incubate overnight, at least 18-24 hours.\n\n","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":27,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"738lc","text":"Add 200 μL ethanol (200 proof) to each tube and mix thoroughly by vortexing followed by a brief pulse spin.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d2v8s","text":"Pipet the mixture from step 14 into a labelled DNeasy Mini spin column. Centrifuge at 6,000xg for 1 minute. Discard flow-through and the collection tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4ohjf","text":"Add 500 μL Buffer AW1, and centrifuge for 1 minute at 6,000xg (8,000rpm). Discard the flow-through and the collection tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"1rnb9","text":"Transfer the spin column to a new collection tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"tso9","text":"Centrifuge for 1 minute at 18,000-20,000 x g (14,000 rpm) to dry.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"68bt","text":"Add 500 μL Buffer AW1, and centrifuge for 1 minute at 6,000xg (8,000rpm). Discard the flow-through and the collection tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7esa8","text":"Add 500 μL Buffer AW2, and centrifuge for 1 minute at 6,000xg (8,000rpm). Discard the flow-through and the collection tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"crf6n","text":"Transfer the spin column to a new collection tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"6dufv","text":"Centrifuge for 1 minute at 18,000-20,000 x g (14,000 rpm) to dry.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2gfo3","text":"Place the spin column in a clean, labelled 1.5 mL microcentrifuge tube. Pipet 100 μL Buffer EB directly onto the DNeasy membrane.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f5ssl","text":"Incubate at room temperature for 1 minute and then centrifuge for 1 minute at 18,000-20,000 x g (14,000 rpm) to elute.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b4qan","text":"Discard spin column and store DNA sample at 4°C for up to 48 hours. For long term storage (\u003e48 hours), store DNA sample at -20°C.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cgn8g","text":"Transfer 1 mL of culture to a labelled microcentrifuge tube and centrifuge at 5,000 g for 10 minutes and remove supernatant.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"74hl7","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"f6qdv","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[{"length":46,"offset":0,"style":"bold"}],"key":"47f9k","text":"This step is high risk for cross-contamination. Clean gloves with 10% bleach in between opening and closing each tube. Continue to take extreme care to avoid cross-contamination throughout the extraction procedure.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cott0","text":"Add 180 μL Buffer ATL to the tube and resuspend the pellet. Add 20 μL Proteinase K to the tube, then vortex.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"8d08b","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"bu5qt","text":"If the ATL buffer solution is cloudy and has precipitate formation, be sure to heat the solution at 50 - 55°C until solution is clear before adding to culture.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"c7ji5","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ca4k0","text":" Incubate at 56°C for a minimum of 1 hour or up to overnight, vortexing periodically.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ffr7l","text":"Optional: Add 4 μL of RNase A to each tube, vortex and then incubate at RT for 3-5 minutes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"82d9k","text":"Add 200 μL Buffer AL to the tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
